          "name": "What is the difference between graded vesting and cliff vesting?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Graded vesting releases options in instalments over the vesting term, such as 25 percent each year for four years, while cliff vesting releases nothing until a single date and then vests the whole grant at once. Graded vesting front loads the accounting charge because early tranches are expensed over shorter periods, so year one cost is higher than under cliff vesting."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How is graded vesting expense recognised under Ind AS 102?",
